"[AppEng] IMC failed - blacklist-transitionplane expects items[,meta]","add-grindable","[AppEng] IMC failed - add-grindable expects itemid,meta,itemid,meta,rotations","[AppEng] IMC failed - "," - is not a valid ICM for AE.","Tile entity name is not registeted: ","[AppEng] BC Integration Disabled.","[AppEng] Mine Factory Reloaded Integration Disabled.","[AppEng] Mine Factory Reloaded Integration Enabled.","[AppEng] TE Integration Disabled.","[Appeng][PostInit] Integration Failure","[AppEng] TE Integration Enabled.",
"Startup Time: ","ms","IronChest.build.major.number","%s.%s.%s build %s","IronChest.build.minor.number","ironChests","cacheRenderingInformation","ocelotsSitOnChests","IronChest.build.revision.number","IronChest has a problem loading it\'s configuration","BlockIronChest","IronChest.build.number","IronChest.build.mcversion","IronChest.","Error while handling data on channel %s from player \'%s\'","Error while handling sync map data from player \'%s\'","gameplay","These options affect the gameplay while using the mod.",
"childMorphs","Can you acquire child mob morphs?\nDisabled by default due to improper morph transitions\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","playerMorphs","Can you acquire player morphs?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","bossMorphs","Can you acquire boss morphs?\nThis is disabled by default due to morphing issues with mobs like the EnderDragon, Twilight Forest\'s Hydra and Naga, etc.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","blacklistedMobs","Prevent players from acquiring these mobs as a morph.\nLeave blank to allow acquisition of all compatible mobs.\nFormatting is as follows: <class>, <class>, <class>\nExample: am2.entities.EntityBattleChicken, biomesoplenty.entities.EntityJungleSpider, thaumcraft.common.entities.monster.EntityWisp",
"whitelistedPlayers","Only allow these players to use the Morph skill.\nLeave blank to allow all players to use the skill.\nFormatting is as follows: <name>, <name>, <name>\nExample: Cojomax99, pahimar, ohaiiChun","disableEarlyGameFlight","Disable the flight ability until a player...\n0 = Enable early game flight\n1 = ...has reached the nether\n2 = ...has killed the Wither","loseMorphsOnDeath","Will you lose your morphs on death?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes, all morphs\n2 = Yes, the morph you\'re currently using","instaMorph",
"Will you insta-morph into a new morph acquired?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","Enable abilities?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","modAbilityPatch","Enable mod mob ability patching?\nThis support is mostly provided by the community and is not officially supported by the mod\nIf a mod mob you like doesn\'t have an ability, you can contribute to the mappings on the Morph Github page.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","forceLocalModAbilityPatch","Force the mod to use the local copy of the ModMobAbilitySupport?\nThis is meant for debugging purposes and for modified local mod mob abilities mappings.\nDo take note that mappings server and clientside are not synched so both ends will require the same mappings.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes",
"modNBTStripper","Enable mod mob NBT Stripping?\nThis support is mostly provided by the community and is not officially supported by the mod\nThe stripper was added to remove non-essential information from the Entity NBT to remove duplicate morphs.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","hostileAbilityMode","Hostile Ability Modes\n0 = Off, hostile mobs attack you despite being morphed.\n1 = Hostile mobs do not attack you if you are a hostile mob.\n2 = Hostile mobs of different types do not attack you if you are a hostile mob but hostile mobs of the same kind do.\n3 = Hostile mobs of the same type do not attack you but hostile mobs of other types attack you.\n4 = Hostile mobs have a decreased detection range around you.\nIf you\'d like to turn on Hostile Ability, I\'d recommend Mode 2 (personal preference)",
"hostileAbilityDistanceCheck","Hostile Ability Distance Check for Hostile Ability Mode 4\nYou have to be *this* close before hostile mobs know you are not one of them.\nDefault: 6","canSleepMorphed","Can you sleep while morphed?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","allowMorphSelection","Requested by SoundLogic\nCan you open the morph GUI?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","client","These options are client only.\nCheck here for key codes for the config: http://www.minecraftwiki.net/wiki/Key_codes","ingameKeybindEditorHook","Allow an ingame keybind editor hook for Morph?\nDisable this only if you have issues in the keybind menu.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes",
"keySelectorUp","Key Code to go up on the selector\nDefault: 26 ([)","keySelectorDown","Key Code to go down on the selector\nDefault: 27 (])","keySelectorLeft","Key Code to go left on the selector\nDefault: 26 ([)","keySelectorRight","Key Code to go right on the selector\nDefault: 27 (])","keySelectorUpHold","Key required to hold to use up key on the selector\n0 = None\n1 = Shift\n2 = Ctrl\n3 = Alt\nDefault: 0","keySelectorDownHold","Key required to hold to use down key on the selector\n0 = None\n1 = Shift\n2 = Ctrl\n3 = Alt\nDefault: 0",
"keySelectorLeftHold","Key required to hold to use left key on the selector\n0 = None\n1 = Shift\n2 = Ctrl\n3 = Alt\nDefault: 1","keySelectorRightHold","Key required to hold to use right key on the selector\n0 = None\n1 = Shift\n2 = Ctrl\n3 = Alt\nDefault: 1","keySelectorSelect","Key Code to select morph on the selector.\nDefault: 28 (Enter/Return)","keySelectorCancel","Key Code to close the selector.\nDefault: 1 (Esc)","keySelectorRemoveMorph","Key Code to remove morph on the selector.\nDelete also works by default\nDefault: 14 (Backspace)",
"keyFavourite","Key Code to favourite/unfavourite morph on the selector and show the radial menu.\nDefault: 41 (` [also known as ~])","handRenderOverride","Allow the mod to override player hand rendering?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","showAbilitiesInGui","Show the abilities the morph has in the GUI?\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","sortMorphs","Sort the morphs in the GUI?\n0 = Order of acquisition (Server default)\n1 = Alphabetically (according to Operating System)\n2 = Alphabetically, and attempt to sort grouped morphs as well\n3 = Most recently used since connecting to the server",
"renderCrosshairInRadialMenu","As per request, render the crosshair position when in the radial menu.\n0 = No\n1 = Yes","playerName","state","/cofh/CoFHWorld.cfg","/cofh/CoFHWorld-Generation.cfg","feature","This allows for custom generation to be specified in the WorldCustomGen.txt file.","AllowCustomGeneration","This allows for vanilla ore generation to be REPLACED. Configure in the \'world.vanilla\' section of the CoFHWorld-Generation.cfg; vanilla defaults have been provided.","ReplaceVanillaGeneration","This will flatten the bedrock layer.",
"FlatBedrock","The number of layers of bedrock to flatten to. (Max: 5)","FlatBedrockLayers","If FlatBedrock is enabled, this will enforce it in previously generated chunks.","RetroactiveFlatBedrock","This will retroactively generate ores in previously generated chunks.","RetroactiveOreGeneration","world.vanilla","This section controls generation specifically related to vanilla Minecraft ores. THESE VALUES ARE USED INSTEAD OF STANDARD GENERATION IF REPLACEMENT IS ENABLED.","lapis","/cofh/WorldCustomGen.txt",
"#This file allows for the addition of custom generation TEMPLATES to World.cfg.\n#Generation parameters are changed inside World.cfg.\n#These values are only used as defaults and in the template comments.\n#\n#Format (TAB DELIMITED): GenType\tName\tBlockID\tBlockMeta\tClusterSize\tNumClusters\tminY\tmaxY\tregen\n#GenType is either UNIFORM or NORMAL. If NORMAL, minY is the average height and maxY is the maximum variance.\n#\n#Creates a template with default values of 4 clusters of 4 ores (1000:0) randomly between y = 32 an"
+"d y = 64. Retrogen Enabled:\n#UNIFORM\ttestUniform\t1000\t0\t4\t4\t32\t64\ttrue\n#\n#Creates a template with default values of 6 clusters of 16 ores (1000:1) in a 32-height Normal Distribution centered at y = 32. RetroGen Disabled:\n#NORMAL\ttestNormal\t1000\t1\t16\t6\t32\t16\tfalse\n#\n","uniform","The WorldCustomGen.txt file has an invalid entry: \'","\'. The ID is too high!","There is a duplicate feature entry name: \'","\' - only the first one will be used.","world.custom.","BlockId","The entry for custom ore \'",
"\' is invalid - the block is null.","BlockMeta","world.custom","<UNIFORM>","MinY","MaxY","<NORMAL>","MeanY","MaxVar"," Generation settings for ","; Defaults: ClusterSize = ",", NumClusters = ","ClusterSize","NumClusters","RetroGen","When a configured block is harvested a chain reaction is initiated to break connected blocks of the same type. Takes durability and health for each block mined.","Inspired by ConnectedDestruction by DaftPVF (currently maintained by bspkrs).","Adding %d:%d (%s) to block whitelist for %s (%s:%s)",
